  <summary date="2017-02-01T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Honors Fred Toyosaburo Korematsu for his loyalty and patriotism to the United States, his work to advocate for the civil liberties of all people of the United States, and his dedication to justice and equality.

Recognizes January 30, 2017, as Fred Korematsu Day of Civil Liberties and the Constitution.

Denounces any governmental effort to discriminate against any individual based on his or her national origin or religion.</summary>
